:R-HSA-1369007  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0008150 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Mammalian ABC transporters are usually found on the plasma membrane and on organelles such as the ER and peroxisome but a small number are also located on the mitochondria. Here they are thought to play roles in heme biosynthesis and iron-sulphur cluster synthesis (Burke & Ardehali 2007)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Mitochondrial ABC transporters" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Jassal, Bijay, 2011-07-04" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: D'Eustachio, P, 2011-08-23" , "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2011-07-04" ;
